{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870043422,"sessionID":"ses_285e7558effen5c2XkmIi1dEtE","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1a64dd001Zt0VumLmX0xxn4","messageID":"msg_d7a1935ee00174C2xG8KGB8FOv","sessionID":"ses_285e7558effen5c2XkmIi1dEtE","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-b473bf4736f942c494010a2e4567d379","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `build` command builds a container image from a packaged agent workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version. The command orchestrates: validating prerequisites, incrementing version metadata, building via Docker SDK, and updating metadata with build results.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: `build` command options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Typer `build` command with configurable options for workspace, proxy, cloud provider, output, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Options and defaults\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n- **WHEN** options are omitted\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`, `show_default=True`)\n  - `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`, `Optional[str]`)\n  - `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`, `Optional[str]`)\n  - `output` = `None` (`--output`, `Optional[str]`)\n  - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace path resolution\n- **GIVEN** `workspace` option is provided\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** `workspace_path` SHALL be resolved as `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging enable\n- **GIVEN** `verbose` is `True`\n- **WHEN** the command runs\n- **THEN** `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)` SHALL be called\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: BuildRuntime class initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct `BuildRuntime` with verbose flag and orchestrate build workflow.\n\n#### Scenario: BuildRuntime constructor\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime` is instantiated\n- **WHEN** `verbose` parameter is passed\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL store `verbose: bool = False` as default and initialize a logger\n\n#### Scenario: Build method entry point\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build(workspace_path, **options)` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL orchestrate: load metadata → validate prerequisites → increment version → build → update metadata → return result dict\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build prerequisites validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate Docker availability and Dockerfile existence before build.\n\n#### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n- **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n- **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Dockerfile existence check\n- **GIVEN** `_validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)` runs\n- **WHEN** `Dockerfile` does not exist at `{workspace_path}/Dockerfile`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating Dockerfile is required\n\n#### Scenario: Metadata load for build\n- **GIVEN** `_validate_build_prerequisites` succeeds\n- **WHEN** metadata is loaded\n- **THEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` SHALL be called and return `AgentMetadata`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Version increment on build\n\nThe system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`) before build and revert on failure.\n\n#### Scenario: Semver patch bump\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"1.2.3\"` or `\"v1.2.3\"`\n- **WHEN** `_increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)` runs\n- **THEN** the version SHALL become `\"1.2.4\"` (patch increment), stripping `v` prefix if present\n\n#### Scenario: Non-semver version handling\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"v1.0\"` or `\"1.0\"` (missing patch)\n- **WHEN** `_increment_version` runs\n- **THEN** the version SHALL append `.1` → `\"v1.0.1\"` or `\"1.0.1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty version fallback\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `None` or empty\n- **WHEN** `_increment_version` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a timestamp-based version or use `\"{version}-1\"` pattern as fallback\n\n#### Scenario: Version rollback on build failure\n- **GIVEN** a successful version increment occurred\n- **WHEN** build fails after increment\n- **THEN** the system SHALL revert metadata.version to original value before exiting with error\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Local Docker build execution\n\nThe system SHALL use Docker SDK to build images with proxy support via build args.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build invocation\n- **GIVEN** `_build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)` is called\n- **WHEN** Docker is available\n- **THEN** `DockerService.build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args)` SHALL be invoked\n\n#### Scenario: Image name and tag\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `agent_name` and incremented `version`\n- **WHEN** building locally\n- **THEN** `image_name` SHALL be `{agent_name}` and `tag` SHALL be `{version}` or `\"latest\"` as default\n\n#### Scenario: Proxy build args\n- **GIVEN** `--proxy` option is provided with URL `\"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"`\n- **WHEN** `_build_local` constructs `build_args`\n- **THEN** `build_args` SHALL include `HTTP_PROXY` and `HTTPS_PROXY` keys with the proxy URL\n\n#### Scenario: Build result extraction\n- **GIVEN** Docker build succeeds\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` returns\n- **THEN** the result SHALL contain: `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build metadata update\n\nThe system SHALL persist build results to `agent_metadata.yaml`.\n\n#### Scenario: Update build metadata\n- **GIVEN** `_update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, build_result, tag)` is called\n- **WHEN** metadata is updated\n- **THEN** `metadata.image` SHALL be set as dict with keys:\n  - `image_name: str`\n  - `image_id: str`\n  - `image_size: str`\n  - `build_time: str`\n  - `tag: str` (default `\"latest\"`)\n\n#### Scenario: Metadata file write\n- **GIVEN** metadata is updated with image info\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: DockerService class\n\nThe system SHALL provide `DockerService` for Docker SDK integration with build, push, and remove operations.\n\n#### Scenario: DockerService constructor\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose: bool = False)` is instantiated\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** `verbose` SHALL be stored and a Docker client SHALL be lazily initialized\n\n#### Scenario: Check Docker available\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n- **WHEN** Docker daemon is running\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `True`\n- **WHEN** Docker daemon is not running or unavailable\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Build image\n- **GIVEN** Docker is running\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag=\"latest\", build_args=None)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  - Use `docker.from_env().api.build()` with path=context_path, dockerfile=dockerfile_path, tag=`{image_name}:{tag}`\n  - Pass `buildargs` from proxy settings\n  - Stream build logs\n  - Return dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n\n#### Scenario: Get image info\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService.get_image_info(image_name)` is called\n- **WHEN** image exists locally\n- **THEN** it SHALL return dict with `image_id`, `image_size` (formatted as human-readable string)\n\n#### Scenario: Push image\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService.push_image(image_name, registry_url=None, username=None, password=None)` is called\n- **WHEN** credentials are provided\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  - Call `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` if username and password are non-empty\n  - Retag image if `registry_url` differs from image name registry\n  - Stream push logs\n  - Return dict with `pushed_image`, `push_time`\n\n#### Scenario: Remove image\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n- **WHEN** removal succeeds\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `True`\n- **WHEN** removal fails\n- **THEN** it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Cloud build placeholder\n\nThe system SHALL provide a placeholder for cloud build mode with `cloud_provider` option.\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build not implemented\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `\"cloud\"` or `--cloud-provider` is specified\n- **WHEN** `_build_cloud` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `NotImplementedError` with message indicating cloud build is not yet implemented\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CLI output and progress display\n\nThe system SHALL display build progress using Rich library.\n\n#### Scenario: Progress spinner during build\n- **GIVEN** `build` command runs\n- **WHEN** Docker build is executing\n- **THEN** a Rich `Progress` spinner SHALL be displayed with status message\n\n#### Scenario: Success output\n- **GIVEN** build completes without exception\n- **WHEN** the command finishes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message with:\n  - `image_name`\n  - `image_id`\n  - `build_time`\n  - `metadata_path` (reported as `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`)\n\n#### Scenario: Build failure handling\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n- **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)` SHALL:\n  - Print `Error building agent: {e}` in red\n  - Print full traceback\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Build failure without verbose\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises\n- **WHEN** `verbose` is `False`\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL print `Error building agent: {e}` in red and exit with code `1` (no traceback)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n\nThe system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions.\n\n#### Scenario: Handle error function\n- **GIVEN** `_handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool)` is called\n- **WHEN** an exception occurs in `build` command\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  - Print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red using Rich\n  - If `verbose` is `True`, print full traceback via `traceback.print_exc()`\n  - Raise `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n#### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n- **GIVEN** a subcommand's local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n- **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n- **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand's `verbose` flag\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentMetadata image field\n\nThe system SHALL extend `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with `image` field for build results.\n\n#### Scenario: Image field definition\n- **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- **WHEN** the model is defined\n- **THEN** `image` SHALL be `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` with default `None`\n\n#### Scenario: Image field structure\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.image` is populated after build\n- **WHEN** examining the dict\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n  - `image_name: str`\n  - `image_id: str`\n  - `image_size: str`\n  - `build_time: str`\n  - `tag: str`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build command integration with pack\n\nThe system SHALL assume `pack` command has been run to generate Dockerfile.\n\n#### Scenario: Pack prerequisite assumption\n- **GIVEN** `build` command is invoked\n- **WHEN** Dockerfile is missing\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` suggesting to run `pack` command first\n\n#### Scenario: Dockerfile location\n- **GIVEN** `pack` generated a Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `build` runs\n- **THEN** Dockerfile SHALL be expected at `{workspace}/Dockerfile`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Output option handling\n\nThe system SHALL support `--output` option for build artifacts destination.\n\n#### Scenario: Output path default\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n- **WHEN** build completes\n- **THEN** artifacts remain in the workspace (metadata updated in-place)\n\n#### Scenario: Output path specified\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is specified as a path\n- **WHEN** build completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL copy or move artifacts to the specified output path (implementation detail per design)\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `DEFAULT_TAG` | `\"latest\"` | `build_runtime.py` | Default image tag when version is None |\n| `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | `120` | `docker_service.py` | Default timeout for Docker operations |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; required for local build |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n| `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and status output |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n| `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Version bump logic |\n| `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Added | `BuildRuntime` class with build orchestration |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Added | `DockerService` for Docker SDK integration |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Modified | Add `build` Typer command |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Modified | Add `image` field to `AgentMetadata` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Modified | Export `BuildRuntime` |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- AR-020 — CLI pack command (prerequisite for Dockerfile)\n- AR-022 — CLI publish command (consumes built image)\n- cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n- cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n- Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `build` command with default options builds image successfully\n- [ ] `--verbose` flag enables DEBUG logging and traceback on error\n- [ ] Docker unavailable raises `RuntimeError` with appropriate message\n- [ ] Missing Dockerfile raises `ValueError` suggesting to run `pack`\n- [ ] Version increment follows semver pattern (X.Y.Z → X.Y.Z+1)\n- [ ] Version rollback occurs when build fails\n- [ ] Proxy option passes build args to Docker\n- [ ] Metadata updated with `image` dict after successful build\n- [ ] `_handle_error` prints error and exits with code 1\n- [ ] Rich Progress spinner displayed during build"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775870043391,"end":1775870043419}}}}
